12 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
13 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
14 Article – Local Government
15 4–414.
16 (a) (1) The chief executive and administrative officer of a municipality that
17 has annexed property shall send a copy of the annexation resolution with the new
18 boundaries to:
19 (i) the clerk or similar official of the municipality;
20 (ii) the clerk of the court in any county in which the municipality is
21 located;
